text: Jemaine Atea Mahana Clement (born 10 January 1974) is a New Zealand comedian, actor and musician. He is best known as one half of the Grammy Award-winning comedy duo Flight of the Conchords with Bret McKenzie. He has starred in movies such as Gentlemen Broncos (2009), Rio (2011), Men in Black 3 (2012), The BFG and Moana (both 2016). Clement was born in Masterton, Wellington Region. He is of Māori ancestry. He has a son with his wife, theatre actress and playwright Miranda Manasiadis. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1974 births Category:Living people Category:Grammy Award winners Category:New Zealand comedians Category:New Zealand movie actors Category:Officers of the New Zealand Order of Merit Category:New Zealand Māori people Category:New Zealand singers Category:New Zealand television actors Category:Actors from Wellington
